To implement the collapsible row feature in your table, you can use some JavaScript/jQuery to toggle the visibility of rows related to the same PO Number. I am assuming you want to collapse the rows under the parent row having the same PO Number.

First, make sure you have included the jQuery library in your HTML file:

```html
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
```

Next, add a class to the button in the parent row, like this:
```html
<button class="collapse-btn">^</button>
```

Now, update the child rows' class to distinguish them from the parent row. Replace `"po-number-{{ $post->PO_Number }}"` with a unique class for each child row, like `"po-child-{{ $post->PO_Number }}"`:

```html
<tr class="{{ ($check->PO_Number != $post->PO_Number) ? 'po-number-' . $post->PO_Number : 'po-child-' . $post->PO_Number }}">
```

Finally, add the following script at the end of your HTML file or right before the closing `</body>` tag:

```html
<script>
$(document).ready(function() {
    $('.collapse-btn').click(function() {
        const parentRow = $(this).closest('tr');
        const poNumber = parentRow.find('input[name*="PO_Number"]').val();

        $('tr.po-child-' + poNumber).toggle();
    });
});
</script>
```

This script will find the button with the "collapse-btn" class, and when clicked, it will toggle the visibility of rows with the same PO Number.

Please note that this implementation is based on the assumption you want to collapse rows with the same PO Number under the parent row. You can adjust the script to better suit your needs if the assumption is incorrect.

